{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-10937/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-10937"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:09:37"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman yells at a man across from her."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-10937","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-10937"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1/969ab000-ff16-4b32-8f0c-43b19a71f2d9","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:20:17.127Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma tells Reynolds to “stop being a child.” Indeed, their relationship has overtones of a mother tending to her child, especially after Alma begins poisoning him and taking care of his recovery. The two appeal to each other because of this willingness to fall into such an unusual dynamic. In Reynolds’s case, he seeks maternal love, something he has missed since his mother’s death at a young age.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:747.5612331081081,183.60430743243248,377.4387668918919,434.72128378378375"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1/684d84e5-2f70-44aa-99a3-ae7d4f14310d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:20:30.911Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Mary Blume notes how the death of Władzio Jaworowski d'Attainville, Cristóbal Balenciaga’s longtime lover, influenced the designer’s work: “To this day, Florette [Balenciaga’s lead saleswoman] says, no one is aware of the almost seismic impact of d’Attainville’s death: ‘If he had lived, the house wouldn’t have been so serious, it wouldn’t have had that weight. There was no one to lighten it up’” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 5). The tension derived from Reynolds’s mother’s death, even if it occurred long ago, also hovers over the House of Woodcock, and it is only Alma’s life energy that can “lighten it up.”</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10937/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:30.956503378378315,27.70059121621621,305.99873310810807,279.2989864864865"}}}]}]}]}